You can use CeTZ for this: [arc](https://cetz-package.github.io/docs/api/draw-functions/shapes/arc), [mark](https://cetz-package.github.io/docs/basics/marks). Combining these, you should be able to draw a curved arrow:

```typ
#import "@preview/cetz:0.3.1"

#cetz.canvas({
  import cetz.draw: *

  arc(
    (0, 0),
    radius: 0.5,
    start: -45deg,
    delta: -270deg,
    mark: (
      end: "straight",
    ),
  )
})
```
